The briefing is structured around three themes:
- **Paradigm shift**: Why agent-native differs fundamentally from traditional 
application design (constitution over blueprint)
- **Architecture**: The agent mesh, pluggable agent kinds, declarative 
permission envelopes, and six safety invariants
- **Why it matters**: How the approach addresses the core challenge of building 
capable yet safe autonomous systems

The note is approximately 800 words and balances accessibility for newcomers 
with technical precision.
